    explanationEn: "Opioid overdose: ABCs first — airway, breathing (bag-valve-mask ventilation), then naloxone. Naloxone: opioid antagonist, rapid onset (2-5 min IV), duration 30-90 min. May need repeat dosing or infusion (shorter half-life than most opioids). Precipitated withdrawal: not life-threatening. Observe for re-sedation.",
    explanationZh: "阿片类药物过量：ABCs优先——气道、呼吸（球囊面罩通气），然后纳洛酮。纳洛酮起效快（2-5min IV）、持续30-90min。可能需重复给药或输注。",
