    question: "A 70-year-old with HTN and DM presents with sudden-onset severe chest pain radiating to the back. BP is 190/100 in the right arm and 140/80 in the left arm. CXR shows widened mediastinum. What is the most likely diagnosis?",
    options: ['Acute aortic dissection (Stanford Type A)', 'Acute MI', 'Pulmonary embolism', 'Tension pneumothorax', 'Esophageal rupture'],
