    question: "A patient presents with right lower quadrant pain, fever, and leukocytosis. On physical exam, pain is referred to the RLQ during palpation of the LLQ. What is this sign called?",
    options: ['Rovsing sign', 'McBurney sign', 'Psoas sign', 'Obturator sign', 'Murphy sign'],
