    explanationEn: "Rovsing sign: palpation of LLQ causes pain in RLQ (suggestive of appendicitis). McBurney sign: tenderness at McBurney point (2/3 from umbilicus to ASIS). Psoas sign: RLQ pain with right hip extension (retrocecal appendix). Obturator sign: RLQ pain with internal rotation of flexed hip (pelvic appendix). Murphy sign: RUQ pain on inspiration (cholecystitis).",
    explanationZh: "Rovsing征：按压LLQ引起RLQ疼痛（提示阑尾炎）。McBurney征：McBurney点压痛。腰大肌征：伸右髋RLQ痛。闭孔肌征：屈髋内旋RLQ痛。Murphy征：吸气RUQ痛。",
